    "#### TP Semanal 4\n",
    "\n",
    "### Enunciado\n",
    "\n",
    "Dise帽ar un filtro pasabajos Chebyshev para obtener una atenuaci贸n de 48 dB para frecuencias mayores a 900 Hz, con una atenuaci贸n m谩xima de 0.4 dB desde continua hasta 300 Hz. ( Ancho de Banda reducido para canal Sub Lows )\n",
    "\n",
    "| $$ \\alpha_{Max} [dB] $$   | $$ \\alpha_{Min} [dB] $$ | $$ f_p [Hz] $$ |  $$ f_s [Hz] $$  |\n",
    "|----------|------|----------|----------|\n",
    "| 0,4      | 48   | 300   | 900   |\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Determinar el orden del filtro y el par谩metro .\n",
    "\n",
    "2. Obtener la expresion completa de la Transferencia NORMALIZADA de T(s)\n",
    "\n",
    "3. Obtener el diagrama de polos y ceros y graficar a mano alzada en forma cualitativa la respuesta de modulo y fase. \n",
    "\n",
    "4. Sintetizar el circuito NORMALIZADO utilizando estructuras KerwinHuelsmanNewcomb (KHN, tambi茅n conocido como Variable de Estado ) saliendo desde la salida V3 como indica el siguiente circuito de referencia: \n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"image26.png\">\n",
    "\n",
    "BONUS\n",
    "\n",
    "    +10  Simulaci贸n num茅rica en python\n",
    "    +10  Simulaci贸n Circuital con los valores DESNORMALIZADOS ( cumpliendo la plantilla pedida )\n",
    "    +10   Presentaci贸n en jupyter notebook"
   ]
  },
  {

   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Orden del Filtro y Parametro $\\epsilon$\n",
    "\n",
    "Dada la ecuacion:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\epsilon^2 = 10^{\\frac{\\alpha_{Max}}{10}}-1$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Reemplazando obtengo $\\epsilon^2 = 0.096$\n",
    "\n",
    "El orden del filtro, lo obtengo iterando de la siguiente ecuacion:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\alpha_{Min}[dB] = 10 log (\\epsilon^2 cosh^2(n cosh^{-1}(w_s))+1)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Obtuve n = 5"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Transferencia Normalizada"

    "import matplotlib\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import scipy.signal as sig\n",
    "import sympy as sp\n",
    "from IPython.display import display, Math\n",
    "\n",
    "from pytc2.sistemas_lineales import bodePlot, tf2sos_analog, pretty_print_SOS, pzmap\n",
    "\n",
    "N = 5\n",
    "ALPHA_MAX = .4\n",
    "\n",
    "# %matplotlib inline\n",
    "# matplotlib.use('Qt5Agg')\n",
    "\n",
    "z,p,k = sig.cheb1ap(N, ALPHA_MAX)\n",
    "num, den = sig.zpk2tf(z,p,k)\n",
    "\n",
    "sos_cheb = tf2sos_analog(num, den)\n",
    "display(Math(\"T(s) = \" + pretty_print_SOS(sos_cheb, mode='omegayq', displaystr=False)))\n",
    "\n",
    "H1 = sig.TransferFunction(num, den)\n",
    "fig1, axs = bodePlot(H1)  # Obtener la figura y las subtramas\n",
    "pzmap(H1)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
